events.text: You wake, feeling a tightly knitted carpet against your cheek. You open your eyes, the world sharpens and you realize you're laying on the floor of a dimly lit office.
Employees at desks, oblivious to your presence, surround you. Their tired faces are illuminated by the phosphorescence of CRTs.
A panic strikes you. You do not know where you are. You do not know who you are.
